photo.description: Elle est visible de tout l'Ouest parisien depuis 1973. Du haut de ses 210 mètres et de son toit-terrasse panoramique, ouvert au public, la tour Montparnasse offre une vue exceptionnelle sur son quartier, Saint-Germain-des-Prés et Paris bien sûr. Elle s'élève sur le site de l'ancienne gare du XIXème siècle qui a laissé place, aujourd'hui, à un ensemble contemporain très animé. My Facebook My 500px Press L to view it in large on black. Press F to favorite it. Captures et reproductions interdites. Tous droits réservés. Corentin Foucaut

photo.description: Tour Maine-Montparnasse (Maine-Montparnasse Tower), also commonly named Tour Montparnasse, is a 210-metre (689 ft) office skyscraper located in the Montparnasse area of Paris, France. Constructed from 1969 to 1972, it was the tallest skyscraper in France until 2011, when it was surpassed in height by the Tour First (231 metres / 758 feet). It is currently the thirteenth tallest building in the European Union. The view from the terrace covers a radius of 40 kilometres (25 mi); aircraft can be seen taking off from Orly Airport. The guard rail, to which various antennae are attached, can be pneumatically lowered in just two minutes to allow helicopters to land. At the time of construction, it was the tallest building in Europe by roof height. The construction of La Grande Arche in La Défense places the tower in a second line of perspective across Paris. Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia (20110820-102907-3403_3407-1000d-pano-a1b2c1d3)
